Rating: 3
I will definitely make this again while basil is plentiful. However, I will make it with the following changes: 1/3 cup light mayo + 1/3 cup plain greek yogurt instead of the 1 cup mayo (seriously?) I also used ground turkey breast (easier to find), added 1 egg & 1/4 cup plain bread crumbs. My recipe made 5 good size burgers, plus 1 baby one, resulting in about 213 calories per burger (bread is extra). The basil sauce really made this very tasty. A few simple substitutions made this a reasonable meal, even if you're not counting calories.

